    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1603641162" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14512395369433943209">Great finale to a great trilogy... What is better: Catton&apos;s three-parter on the War Between the States, or Shelby Foote&apos;s trifecta? Both are lyrical masterpieces, both are comprehensive, but I&apos;m going to go with Catton. It&apos;s a matter of personal preference, but I don&apos;t like getting bogged down in exact timetables of battle, e.g. which general was on top of which hill with what troops, etc. </span>
  <span id="freeText14512395369433943209" style="display:none">Great finale to a great trilogy... What is better: Catton's three-parter on the War Between the States, or Shelby Foote's trifecta? Both are lyrical masterpieces, both are comprehensive, but I'm going to go with Catton. It's a matter of personal preference, but I don't like getting bogged down in exact timetables of battle, e.g. which general was on top of which hill with what troops, etc. </span>
